# Identifiy Necessary Tools and Services
Flask: Lightweight web framework for Python.
PostgreSQL: Relational database system.
GitHub: Version control and repository hosting.
Bootstrap: Front-end UI styling.
AWS: For production environment hosting.

Flask: Chosen due to its simplicity and quick setup for a small-scale web application. It has a lower learning curve compared to other frameworks like Django.
PostgreSQL: Provides robust relational database support with strong community backing. Ideal for handling structured data.
AWS: Offers flexible hosting with various pricing tiers, making it suitable for production deployment.
